Renovations on the elephant facility began 2007.<ref name=zoo-elephant>{{cite web | url = http://www.marylandzoo.org/animals-conservation/elephant-program/ | title = Elephant Program | publisher = The Maryland Zoo in Baltimore | accessdate = 28 November 2012}}</ref> In March 2006, the Maryland Zoo announced<ref>{{cite press release | url = http://www.marylandzoo.org/images/news/pdf/Maryland%20Zoo%20Elephant%20Program%20Expansion%20Press%20Release%20_2_.pdf | publisher = Maryland Zoo | title = Elephant Program Expansion | date = March 2006 | access-date = 2014-04-21 | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20070928082838/http://www.marylandzoo.org/images/news/pdf/Maryland%20Zoo%20Elephant%20Program%20Expansion%20Press%20Release%20_2_.pdf | archive-date = 2007-09-28 | dead-url = yes }}</ref> it would be accepting three female [[African_elephant|African elephant]]s from the [[Philadelphia_Zoo|Philadelphia Zoo]] as part of the expanded elephant exhibit, but construction was then delayed and the elephant loan was canceled.<ref>{{cite press release | url = http://www.marylandzoo.org/images/news/pdf/Maryland%20Zoo%20Elephant%20Announcement%20Press%20Release.pdf | publisher = Maryland Zoo | title = Elephant Announcement | date =  | access-date = 2014-04-21 | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20070928082829/http://www.marylandzoo.org/images/news/pdf/Maryland%20Zoo%20Elephant%20Announcement%20Press%20Release.pdf | archive-date = 2007-09-28 | dead-url = yes }}</ref> However, two new elephants came to the Maryland Zoo from Arkansas in 2007.<ref name=zoo-elephant/> On March 19, 2008, Felix, one of the zoo's female elephants, gave birth to a 290-pound male calf, the first elephant born in the zoo's history. The baby is named Samson and is now viewable, weather permitting.

