===Maryland Wilderness featuring The Children's Zoo===
Displaying animals found in Maryland, visitors can watch [[otter|otter]]s swim over their heads, jump across lily pads, explore a cave, or climb into giant bird nests.

*'''The Bog''': features the [[bog_turtle|bog turtle]], an endangered species.
*'''Marsh Aviary & Lily Pads''': surrounds a man-made stream featuring many species of ducks and other Maryland birds.
*'''The Stream''': includes [[North_American_River_Otter|river otters]] and [[red_fox|red fox]].  You can visit a submerged archway, and watch as otters swim overhead.
*'''The Cave''': a beautifully sculpted life-size model of a cave, featuring more than a dozen small exhibits including [[snake|snake]]s, [[bat|bat]]s, and [[newts|newts]].
*'''Giant Tree & Slide''': features many native reptiles and amphibians animals, mainly [[snake|snake]]s.  The slide is a fun way for kids to get back to the ground.
*'''Meadow''': has animals such as [[box_turtles|box turtles]] and [[American_toad|American toad]]s.  Kids can poke their heads in large bubble-like windows coming out of the ground.
*'''The Farmyard''': features a variety of rare domestic breeds that can be touched; the highlight is a petting area of friendly [[Pygmy_goat|African pygmy goat]]s and [[Nubian_goat|Nubian goat]]s called "The Kid Zone" because young goats are called kids and it also attracts children.  Other animals included in the section include [[Jacob_(sheep)|Jacob sheep]], [[donkey|donkey]], [[barn_owl|barn owl]], [[chicken|chicken]], [[Anser_(genus)|geese]], [[pig|pig]], and [[Dexter_cattle|Dexter cattle]]. 

The Maryland Wilderness featuring The Children's Zoo is dedicated to Lyn P. Meyerhoff.

