===Polar Bear Watch===
The Polar Bear Watch features [[polar_bear|polar bear]]s named Magnet and Anoki, as well as [[raven|raven]]s and [[arctic_fox|arctic fox]]es.  Guests can view bears from underwater viewing areas, or from the windows of an actual massive [[Tundra_Buggy|Tundra Buggy]], purchased from the Canadian company that creates these one of kind vehicles for viewing Polar Bears in their natural habitat.<ref>{{cite press release|url=http://www.tundrabuggy.com/news/polar-bear-watch-at-the-baltimore-zoo|title=Polar Bear Watch at the Baltimore Zoo|publisher=Frontiers North Adventures|accessdate=2009-10-11}}</ref>

Magnet won a contest put forth by Microsoft's Zoo Tycoon for best zoo animal. Magnet was available as a downloadable patch for the game and during the game, polar bears purchased via the Magnet icon would play with a red ball.<ref>{{cite news|location = Baltimore, Maryland | title = Baltimore Zoo polar bear wins Microsoft promotional competition for new computer game|date=December 14, 2001 |work=The Daily Record|accessdate=2009-10-11}}</ref>

===Base Camp Discovery===
Base Camp Discovery is located between the Polar Bear Watch and the African Journey.  There, educational activities and various animal ambassadors are presented by zoo educators.  Animals that are often shown at Base Camp Discovery include the [[boa_constrictor|boa constrictor]], [[Egyptian_tortoise|Egyptian tortoise]], [[painted_turtle|painted turtle]], [[box_turtle|box turtle]], [[diamondback_terrapin|diamondback terrapin]], [[corn_snake|corn snake]], [[blue_and_gold_macaw|blue and gold macaw]], [[African_gray_parrot|African gray parrot]], [[Indian_runner_duck|Indian runner duck]], and [[eastern_screech_owl|eastern screech owl]], among many others.
